<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Open Handset Alliance'); ?>
        <p>The <strong>Open Handset Alliance (OHA)</strong> is a consortium of 84 firms to develop open standards for mobile devices. Member firms include <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Google', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTC', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Sony', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Dell', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Intel', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Motorola', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Qualcomm', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Texas Instruments', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Samsung Electronics', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('LG Electronics', 'C'); ?>, T-Mobile, Sprint Corporation, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Nvidia', 'C'); ?>, and Wind River Systems.</p>
        <p>The OHA was established on 5 November 2007, led by Google with 34 members, including mobile handset makers, application developers, some mobile carriers and chip makers. <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Android', 'OS'); ?>, the flagship software of the alliance, is based on an open-source license and has competed against mobile platforms from <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Apple', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Nokia', 'C'); ?> (Symbian), <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HP', 'C'); ?> (formerly Palm), <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Samsung Electronics', 'C'); ?> / <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Intel', 'C'); ?> (Tizen, bada), and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('BlackBerry', 'C'); ?>.</p>
        <p>As part of its efforts to promote a unified Android platform, OHA members are contractually forbidden from producing devices that are based on incompatible forks of Android.</p>
    </div>
</div>